4.21	Fazal_Mahmood	Fazal Mahmood	Fazal Mahmood (18 February 1927 â€“ 30 May 2005) was a Pakistani cricketer, regarded as the finest pace bowler of his country's early years. He played in 34 Test matches and took 139 wickets at a bowling average of 24.70. The first Pakistani to pass 100 wickets, he reached the landmark in his 22nd match.	
